# Intake — CivicQ Landing Page Build

## Client & Project Identity

**Client:** CivicQ (nonpartisan civic information platform)
**Deliverable:** Public-facing home page + methodology page at civicq.org
**Positioning:** Michael is an expert US-based front-end developer (✓ qualified; note in proposal) extending an existing staging dark-mode design system, building to spec, not redesigning
**Brand identity:** Nonpartisan, civic-tech, "no spin just the record," data-forward, transparent, factual, official tone
**Budget range:** $3,500–$5,000 fixed price (milestone payments welcome)
**Timeline:** 2–4 weeks from start; hard launch dependency on GoFundMe campaign
**Target feature richness:** 10/10 (full-featured, production-quality, complete landing page built to spec with all three custom data visualizations working)

---

## The Deliverable — 10-Section Landing Page + /methodology Page

### Main Page (civicq.org) — 10 sections with sticky navigation

1. **Hero**
   - Video thumbnail
   - Primary CTA + secondary CTA
   - Keyword: "no spin, just the record" sensibility

2. **Problem Statement**
   - Single-column text
   - Frames the need for civic transparency

3. **Feature Card Grid**
   - 2×2 grid (4 features)
   - LIVE / IN DEVELOPMENT status pills on each
   - Signals honesty about current vs. roadmap features

4. **Scoring Methodology Visualization**
   - Custom 6-dimension weighted chart (SVG or Recharts/D3)
   - Must clearly show weights; interactive/animated preferred
   - Explains how CivicQ scores voting/bill/statement data

5. **Honest Status Disclosure**
   - Two-column layout: LIVE (what works now) vs. IN DEVELOPMENT (what's coming)
   - Emphasizes radical transparency

6. **Organization Hub Section**
   - Wireframe mockup included
   - Email capture form (Mailchimp/ConvertKit level, but with CSV backup export)
   - Positioning: for orgs/researchers who want deeper access

7. **Fundraising Module**
   - $75K funds-breakdown graphic (custom data viz, coded)
   - Sum must total $75K; readable at a glance
   - GoFundMe CTA (link provided by client)
   - **Hard launch dependency:** this is launch-blocking

8. **Partners / Press / Orgs**
   - Three-column card section
   - Lists and links

9. **Feedback Banner + Footer**
   - Sticky feedback call-out
   - Footer with nav links, copyright, etc.

10. **Sticky Navigation**
    - Anchor links to all 10 sections above
    - Active section highlighting on scroll
    - Integrates with existing search/auth UI

### Secondary Page: /methodology

- Dedicated page at civicq.org/methodology
- Content provided by client (structured drop-in doc)
- Same dark-mode design system, responsive, accessible

---

## Hard Requirements (Grading Checklist)

### Stack & Environment
- **React or Next.js** (client lists both; Next.js is preferred for SEO + structure)
- **JavaScript**
- Integrate with existing staging environment and design system

### Design & Styling
- **Dark-mode design system matched precisely; NOT redesigned**
- Existing tokens/palette/typography provided to the hired dev (unavailable to us; demo uses a faithful stand-in civic-tech dark theme)
- Restrained, neutral, institutional aesthetic (no partisan color coding, no loaded language)
- Nonpartisan in every pixel and word

### Responsive & Performance
- **Fully responsive:** 390px (mobile) and 1440px (desktop), fluid in between
- **Lighthouse 85+ on mobile** (accessibility, performance, best practices)
- Lean build; no unnecessary animation or bloat

### Data Visualizations (3 required, all coded)
1. **Six-dimension weighted scoring chart**
   - Bar, donut, or radar chart showing weights clearly
   - Interactive/animated preferred but functional clarity is required
   - Built from scratch with SVG or Recharts/D3; no pre-built component

2. **$75K Funds Breakdown Graphic**
   - Pie, bar, or stacked chart summing to exactly $75K
   - Readable at a glance; shows allocation across categories
   - Accessible to low vision / color-blind users

3. **Organization Hub Wireframe Mockup**
   - Looks like an intentional product design, not a gray box
   - Shows what org access/research features might look like
   - Illustrative but appears production-ready

### Forms & Backend Integration
- **Email Capture Form**
  - Mailchimp/ConvertKit level integration
  - **CSV export / backup capability required**
  - On success: clear confirmation, no page reload on submission
  - Validating (email required, basic checks)

- **Backend expectation:** Demo should wire mw-backend with a civicq_blueprint.py
  - POST /subscribe: store email + timestamp to DB
  - GET /csv-export: return all emails as CSV
  - This proves the "CSV backup" requirement with working persistence

### Analytics
- **Plausible or Fathom preferred** (privacy-respecting)
- Lightweight event hooks in place (placeholder implementation is OK; signals best practices)
- Page view tracking at minimum

### Accessibility
- **WCAG 2.1 AA** minimum
- Semantic HTML (nav, section, main landmarks)
- Focus states (keyboard nav visible)
- Color contrast ≥4.5:1 for text; ≥3:1 for large text
- Alt text on all images
- ARIA labels where needed (button purposes, status pills, etc.)
- Respects prefers-reduced-motion
- Form labels properly associated

