## Scope & Token Budget

**Demo scope (fitting 10/10 richness):**
- Hero feature: complete 10-section landing page + /methodology page with sticky anchor nav
- Supporting feature 1: three coded data visualizations (all working, accessible, interactive)
- Supporting feature 2: working email capture + CSV export backend integration
- Minor support: LIVE/IN-DEV status pills, two-column disclosures, responsive polish, analytics hooks, a11y audit

**Token budget constraints:**
- Demo touches ≤~12 files (index.html + CSS + JS; if Vite: src/App.jsx, pages, components, hooks, assets)
- Build timeout: 3 min
- Research fetches: ≤~6 (civic-tech platforms, nonprofit dark-mode patterns, Recharts docs)
- Reflection retries: ≤2

**Design constraints:**
- Use existing mw-backend as backend scaffold (copy spotify_blueprint.py pattern for civicq_blueprint.py)
- Demo form: self-contained static app or small Vite React build (base: '/demos/civicq/')
- Deploy to ../michaelwegter.com/public/demos/civicq/

